{"id": 225001716, "title": "River Hill High&#8217;s Jessica Nichols named Howard Teacher of the Year", "text": "River Hill High School teacher Jessica Nichols was named the 2024 Howard County Public School System Teacher of the Year. Nichols was named during a surprise visit by school system officials to River Hill and also recognized at a recent Board of Education meeting, according to a news release. \u201cWhen I received the news that I was Teacher of the Year, I was completely overwhelmed with joy,\u201d she wrote in an email. \u201cI am so grateful to my students who nominated me for this award. This is an amazing honor, and I am humbled to be one of the Howard County Teachers of the Year.\u201d Nichols has been a secondary social studies teacher since 2001, according to the release. She taught in Montgomery County Public Schools and at a private academy before joining the social studies department at River Hill High School in 2014. While there, she has been the head sponsor of several clubs and served as the school\u2019s wellness representative as a teacher development liaison. At a board of education meeting April 25, Acting Superintendent William Barnes recognized Nichols for her award. \u201cI was so honored to celebrate Jessica alongside her students and colleagues at River Hill and it was immediately apparent how well-loved and respected she is in that building,\u201d Barnes said. \u201cShe clearly has an instrumental impact on those she serves and, as her student noted, it will influence their trajectory for the rest of their lives.\u201d Nichols has been described by staff members and students as \u201ccaring,\u201d \u201ckind,\u201d and \u201cselfless,\u201d according to the release, and her students say that she engages and inspires them with anecdotes and stories that help bring lessons to life. One of her students wrote in their nomination: \u201cMrs. Nichols has sacrificed countless hours to show up for her students\u2019 events, games, and celebrations \u2026 She never fails to make time for her students \u2026 She goes above and beyond her classroom duties, supporting and teaching her students in ways that impact them for the rest of their lives, because she truly cares about each and every one of them.\u201d The school system also announced that it had named Joelle Miller of Centennial High School as Principal of the Year and Jeanette Swank of Ellicott Mills Middle School, a teacher of the year. Swank will represent Howard County in the Washington Post Teacher of the Year program and Nichols will represent Howard in the Maryland State Department of Education Teacher of the Year program.", "summary": "River Hill High School teacher Jessica Nichols was named the 2024 Howard County Public School System Teacher of the Year.", "url": "https://www.baltimoresun.com/2024/05/29/river-hill-highs-jessica-nichols-named-howard-teacher-of-the-year/", "image": "https://www.baltimoresun.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/HOW-L-NICHOLSTEACHEROFTHEYEAR.jpg?w=1024", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:00:54", "author": "Allana Haynes", "authors": ["Allana Haynes"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.679}